examples: I agree to perform residence premove surveys on domestic shipments estimated at 4,700 pounds or more, and/or international shipments estimated at 3,200 pounds or more, at origin points within a 50-mile radius of my nearest agent facility.

entries.meaning: (Internet chess) On certain chess websites: a move set during the opponent's turn which is played automatically (if possible) after the opponent has made their move, done in order to save time in predictable positions.

verbs.description: premove (third-person singular simple present premoves, present participle premoving, simple past and past participle premoved)

entries.meaning: (philosophy, theology, rare) To incite or cause someone to do something.
